'''Our Stories Films''' is an [[United States|American]] [[film studio]] founded on July 13, 2006 by [[Robert L. Johnson]] producing "[[comedy film|comedic]], family-friendly feature films for [[African American]] and urban audiences". It began as a joint venture between [[RLJ Companies]] and [[The Weinstein Company]].<ref name="BE">{{cite news|url=http://www.blackenterprise.com/cms/exclusivesopen.aspx?id=1769&p=0 |title=Robert Johnson Gets the Green Light |accessdate=2007-05-11 |first=Joyce |last=Jones |authorlink= |coauthors= |date=2006-07-19 |year= |month= |format= |work=[[Black Enterprise]] |pages= |language= |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070928060917/http://www.blackenterprise.com/cms/exclusivesopen.aspx?id=1769&p=0 |archivedate = 2007-09-28 |quote= }}</ref><ref>"PRNewswire" [http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/the-rlj-companies-launches-our-stories-films-in-association-with-the-weinstein-company-69933637.html The RLJ Companies Launches 'Our Stories Films' in Association With The Weinstein Company] prnewswire.com, Retrieved on November 12, 2012</ref> On August 31, 2006, it was announced that [[Tracey Edmonds]] was named president and chief operating officer of Our Stories Films, making her the first African American to head a film studio.<ref name="BE2">{{cite news|url=http://www.blackenterprise.com/cms/exclusivesopen.aspx?id=1870 |title=Tracey Edmonds to Lead Our Stories Films |accessdate=2007-05-11 |first=Joyce |last=Jones |authorlink= |coauthors= |date=2006-08-31 |year= |month= |format= |work=[[Black Enterprise]] |pages= |language= |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070311032757/http://www.blackenterprise.com/cms/exclusivesopen.aspx?id=1870 |archivedate = 2007-03-11 |quote= }}</ref>
The studio's first film, ''[[Who's Your Caddy?]]'', was released on July 28, 2007.
On May 6, 2011, Our Stories Films released ''[[Jumping the Broom]]'' through [[TriStar Pictures]] and opened to mixed reviews, but had a highly successful opening weekend box office number. Kevin Thomas of the [[Los Angeles Times]] gave ''Jumping the Broom'' a positive review however, and called it: "An exuberant comedy. Fun, smart, and heart tugging with a sparkling ensemble cast." ''Jumping the Broom'' was released on [[DVD]] and [[Blu-ray Disc|Blu-ray]] on August 9, 2011.
